main event: A 9-year-old witness saw two objects in the sky in Union, New Jersey on April 7, 1966. One object appeared glowing and round, while the other was elongated and blinking. The objects moved rapidly and then accelerated and disappeared.
interesting points: The glowing object moved rapidly from right to left, then accelerated and disappeared.
The elongated object moved slowly, blinking, and then also accelerated and disappeared.
The witness took several photos of the objects, but none of the photos are clear enough to show the details.
The witness reported the sighting to the local police department.
The witness described the objects as a 9-inch white luminous object trailing orange coloring at high altitude.
sighted object: Two unidentified aerial objects, one glowing and round, the other elongated and blinking
